						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Banshaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So maybe using CHR-RAM for an action game is maybe not a good reason after all and I should stick to rom only.</div>
<br />There's nothing wrong with using CHR-RAM for an action game, provided you manage it properly.
<br />
<br />Battletoads is a good example of <em>great</em> CHR-RAM management.
<br />Strider is a good example of <em>awful</em> CHR-RAM management. (PROTIP: you can't store two different tiles in the same spot <em>at the same time,</em> Capcom!)</div>

					
